<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>English Heritage – Written evidence</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">English Heritage – Written evidence</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Summar</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">y</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage is very mindful of the need for e</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">conomic vitality</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> in all aspects of its work. Economic sustainability</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">key</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> to heritage conservation and heritage makes an important contribution to it. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage consults with business very regularly to understand how to optimise the relationship between </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">viable use of historic places</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and conservation.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The planning system is geared towards achieving ‘sustainable development’. This is defined in the National Planning Policy Framework</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">sets out how heritage conservation should be achieved within a vibrant economy. English Heritage gives all its advice with this objective in mind. It is subject to a duty as part of its funding arrangements with the Department for Culture Media and Sport to promote such sustainable development.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">also</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">obliged to follow</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> the Regulators’ Code (under the Regulatory and Legislative Reform Act 2006</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> guidance issued by the Department for Business Innovation and Skills entitled</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Accountability for Regulator Impact</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">he</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> broad</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> aim of</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> both</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> is</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">to ensure that regulators engage with businesses which they affect</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> so as to understand the economic</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and other</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> impact</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> of the way in which they </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">might carry out their functions</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">has published a</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">n Improvement Plan for Planning Services to minimise adverse impacts on business from our role in the planning system, particularly in terms of costs on key planning projects and development more generally.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage’s </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">direct regulatory powers </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">actually </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">very limited. The use of these powers is very infrequent (one case in the past twelve months)</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">e impact of those regulatory activities</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> on the wider economy</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> is negligible. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage exercises its influence through advice and guidance to central and local government, principally in the operation of the planning system. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Our regular dialogue</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and formal consultation </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">with </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">business is intended to ensure </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">that we are aware of business concerns about our work</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. We obviously understand the connection between business and regulatory efficiency and good conservation outcomes. We work hard to understand the concerns of those whom our advice and guidance affects. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">he duty to have regard to growth </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">as it appears in the draft Bill </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">will </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">be in keeping with the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">considerations English Heritage has always brought to bear in its pursuit of sustainable heritage conservation. It will also be in keeping with </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">existing obligations on English Heritage</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Given the several existing obligations on English Heritage that cover the same territory as the proposed duty, we are concerned by the potential for </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">confusion as to how compliance with each should be achieved and of overlapping reporting requirements. We would be very keen to see </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">consolidation of guidance and reporting obligations as far as possible. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Heritage and Growth</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">9</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Conservation of all heritage assets relies, albeit to differing degrees, on ongoing maintenance and therefore ongoing investment. Economic vitality is therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">key</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> to the overall success of conservation in England. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">10</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Our heritage is a major contributor to economic vitality. It provides income to the country through tourism and is frequently the seed-corn of successful, characterful and sustainable regeneration of run-down areas. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">11</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The vast majority of heritage assets are in private hands. The conservation of such assets depends on the motivation of the owners, which in large part will be dictated by their own economics. It is therefore vital that all those involved in conservation understand the position of owners, including businesses, and work with them to find constructive ways of conserving heritage assets – ways that sustain the important heritage value of the asset, whilst providing it with a viable use for the medium to long term.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">‘Sustainable Development’, Conservation and Growth</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">12</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The National Planning Policy Framework (the NPPF) provides a definition of ‘sustainable development’ and policies for planning decisions that encapsulates the tie-in between economic vitality and heritage conservation. It thoughtfully sets out the way in which those twin objectives should be sought in </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">way that maximises the potential for both, whilst minimising conflict.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">13</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The NPPF effectively governs a great deal of the work that English Heritage is involved in. Where it does not directly apply as a matter of law, English Heritage still sees its principles as applying as a matter of consistent common sense.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">14</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Applying the principles of the NPPF to the work of conservation requires all decision-makers involved in the planning system to be mindful of the objective of heritage regulation and of growth.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">English Heritage’s Engagement with Business</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">15</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">It has always been vital to the success of English Heritage’s work that it understands the position and motivations of owners and that</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> through that</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> it understands the impact of its activities. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">16</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage has very good ongoing relations with representatives of owners and developers across the spectrum of relevant property concerns. Bodies such as the Country Land and Business Association, the British Property Federation and the Historic Houses Association are in very regular contact informally and formally through the Historic Environment Forum. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Chair of English Heritage has frequent meetings with these bodies to ensure that the corporate strategy takes in their concerns. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">17</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">They are consulted on all matters of concern to them. They </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">have been </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">active participants in the drafting of guidance to support the NPPF. Business is also represented on the National Heritage Protection Plan (NHPP) Advisory Board. The NHPP is a means by which English Heritage prioritises its areas of work. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">18</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Owners and developers are represented on English Heritage’s governing body (the Commission) and its statutory advisory committees.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">19</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage also has its own experience to draw on as the operator of a heritage attraction business covering over 400 properties with a turnover in excess of £50m. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">English Heritage as a Regulator</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">20</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage’s role in the protection of the historic environment is frequently misunderstood. English Heritage is principally an expert adviser. It is not a decision-maker in the planning system. Its regulatory activities are very limited:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:16.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage has a power to prosecute offences under the Ancient Monuments and Archaeological Areas Act 1979 and the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990. In the past 12 months (not an untypical year) one prosecution under the 1979 Act and none under the 1990 Act was undertaken. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:16.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage may apply for an injunction to prevent any such breaches of the law. None was applied for in the last year. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:16.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">In Greater London only, English Heritage has the power to direct local planning authorities to refuse listed building consent. It also has certain powers to execute works and compulsorily acquire listed buildings at risk in Greater London. None of these powers was used in the last year. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:16.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage has some limited powers of entry onto land for the purposes of compiling records. None was used in the last year.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">21</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We currently publish around 15 pieces of general advice and guidance annually and are asked to respond to around 22,000 cases from around the country. From this arises an average of around 50 complaints yearly, of which an average of around 5 turn into a threat of judicial review or JR proceedings. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">22</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage is </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">very active in providing advice and guidance to local planning authorities as to the best means of achieving the objectives of the NPPF at the strategic level of making local development plans and on a case-by-case basis. Local planning authorities are bound to take into account such advice in so far as it is in keeping with the NPPF and their existing local development plans. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">23</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">As the NPPF and local plans are all directed to the objective of sustainable development, which already has the objectives of growth and heritage conservation (amongst others) written into it, English Heritage’s advice </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">has to be</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> mindful of both the conservation and growth impacts. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">24</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage is not responsible for any system of compliance. The impact of its regulatory activities is very limited indeed and in the last year has been negligible.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Regulators’ Code 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">25</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage is subject to the Regulators’ Code 2013. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">This sets out the guidance on how regulators have regard to the Code when developing policies and operational procedures that guide their regulatory activities. In particular:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should carry out their activities in a way that supports those they regulate to comply and grow </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should provide simple and straightforward ways to engage with those they regulate and hear their views </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should base their regulatory activities on risk </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should share information about compliance and risk</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should ensure clear information, guidance and advice is available to help those they regulate meet their responsibilities to comply</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Regulators should ensure that their approach to their regulatory activities is transparent </span></li></ul></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">26</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ese are actions </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">English Heritage wholeheartedly supports</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> not only because they are obvious actions to support successful heritage conservation</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> but </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">also </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">because they reinforce</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> the balanced definition of sustainable development within the NPPF.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">27</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">For </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">nine</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> years we have</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> publish</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> a Charter </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">for Planning Services </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">(now in its 5</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:8pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> edition) </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">which</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> sets out the service provided by English Heritage for those involved in changing or influencing change to the historic environment. It explains how we handle requests for pre-application and statutory advice; it covers our advice on matters of policy and management issues relevant to the planning process; and it explains our engagement, in partnership with others, in the modernised planning system.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">The value and impact of a new statutory duty to have regard to growth</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">28</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Given the several existing obligations on English Heritage that cover the same territory as the proposed duty, we are concerned by the potential for confusion as to how compliance with each should be achieved and of overlapping reporting requirements. We would be very keen to see consolidation of guidance and reporting obligations as far as possible. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:normal">29</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We also have residual concerns about how the duty </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">may</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> be perceived. As drafted it should not impede the primary statutory objectives of English Heritage’s work. However, if the wording </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">was </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">changed or</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> if</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> the supporting guidance altered the interpretation and the result was </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">an unresolved potential conflict between the primary regulatory objectives and the growth duty, then there could be considerable implications for the work of English Heritage and challenges to it. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">In answer to the specific questions on the Deregulation Bill</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Questions</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">General</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">1. The draft Bill covers a broad range of specific activities and a large amount of legislative provision is amended by it. Could the same result have been achieved using existing secondary legislative procedures? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above regarding existing obligations that achieve similar objectives. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">2. What are the advantages and disadvantages of including specific deregulatory provisions amending existing legislation and providing additional or amended order making powers within primary legislation rather than considering them through existing deregulatory mechanisms? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">3. Are the changes proposed in the draft Bill evidence-based and have any risks associated with the changes been taken adequately into account? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">4. Does the draft Bill achieve its purpose of reducing the regulatory burden on business, organisations and individuals effectively and fairly?</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above. We do not believe it will materially</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> alter</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">effect</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> of English Heritage’s advice and guidance as the economic impact of such is already well considered</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">5. Will the draft Bill generally benefit businesses by offsetting other regulatory burdens? Are there indirect impacts on other businesses from reducing regulation in specific sectors? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">6. To what extent does the draft Bill benefit consumers as well as businesses? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">7. How does the provision in the draft Bill affect: </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">i</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. protections afforded to individuals under human rights and equalities legislation? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ii</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. employment law, skills and the labour market? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">iii</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. the environment, particularly in the management of waste? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">iv. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">the</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> provision of education? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">v</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">. the effective administration of justice? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 108pt; text-indent:-9pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">vi. </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">social</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">, wellbeing or health inequalities? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">8. Have the measures set out in the draft Bill been subject to adequate cost-benefit analysis on the basis of consultation with those affected? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">9. Will any or all of the proposals have any significant economic or financial impact? Do you have any evidence of the impact that will aid the Committee in their scrutiny? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Power to disapply legislation no longer of practical use </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">10. Is a new “power to disapply legislation no longer of practical use” necessary or are there existing procedures which could be used to achieve the same effect?” </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(Clause 51)?</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">11. Is the </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">meaning of the phrase “no longer of practical use” clear</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">? In this context, what is meant by “practical”? </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Should it be defined and, if so, how?</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> Will removing any of the provision proposed in Schedule 16 of the draft Bill have implications for any other areas of regulation? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">12. Are the safeguards regarding the use of the “no longer of practical use” power (set out in Clauses 54 to 56) adequate and appropriate? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">13. Other deregulatory mechanisms such as Legislative Reform Orders or Public Bodies Orders have specific tests set out in the parent Act - should there be similar tests set out in the draft Bill? What should they be? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">14. Are the mechanisms set out for parliamentary oversight (Clauses 55 and 56) of deregulation orders adequate and appropriate? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">15. Are there other changes to deregulatory powers, procedures and parliamentary oversight which you think should have been included in the Bill and, if so, why?</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">16. What are the risks associated with the proposed new power to disapply legislation that is “no longer of practical use”? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">A duty to have regard to the desirability of promoting economic growth </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">17. To what extent do the Government’s existing powers of direction over regulators already provide the ability to guide regulators towards the importance of promoting economic growth? Is this legislation necessary? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">18. Will the introduction of a duty to have </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">regard</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> to “promoting economic growth” compromise the independence of regulators? What additional safeguards are required to ensure that the introduction of such a duty will not compromise the independence of a regulator? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">19. How is a duty to have regard to the desirability of economic growth likely to affect those regulators to which it is applied? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We believe it will impact where there is more than one way of achieving satisfactory compliance. In such circumstances it is obviously important to understand which means of regulation would be the least burdensome and the most supportive of growth. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">As commented above, understanding the impact of heritage guidance is fundamental to achieving successful conservation. It is also part of existing compliance and reporting regimes to which English Heritage is subject. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">20. Where is the introduction of such a duty likely to have beneficial effect? Where might there be adverse consequences? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above. Provided the duty is interpreted as we understand it at present and the guidance on how to comply and reporting regimes are </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">consolidated and harmonised with similar requirements already in existence, the impact should be neutral.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">21. How might the extent to which a regulator has fulfilled, or breached, the duty be ascertained? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">See comments above. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">22. How can the likely financial and economic impact of the proposed duty be assessed? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Devolution </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">23. What are the consequences of the draft Bill for the devolved administrations? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">-</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'